KW  - Savings and loans
KW  - Ownership structure
KW  - Expense-preference
KW  - Financial institutions
AB  - This note demonstrates that the conclusion of the Akella and Greenbaum (1988) study that managers of mutual S&Ls exhibit more expense-preference behavior than managers of stockholder-owned S&Ls is premature. It is shown that, in operationalizing their theoretical model, A & G introduce an endogenous variable in their correction for homogeneity, invalidating their results. The only firm conclusion which can be drawn from their results is that a higher proportion of assets of mutual S&Ls is invested in loans while a higher proportion of liabilities are sourced from deposits than is the case for stockholder-owned S & Ls.
ER  - 

